main event: A civilian observer reported seeing a glowing mass of four square lights over New Windsor, New York on March 30, 1967.
interesting points: The object was compared in size to six stars put together.
The object had a soft humming noise.
The object moved from south to east and then to the northeast before disappearing slowly.
The object was visible for 4-5 minutes.
The 12-year-old civilian observer was considered a poor reliability source.
sighted object: glowing mass of four square lights
